data.chText: （通过努力、能力、行为表现）获得，得到
data.enText: to gain sth by your own efforts, ability or behaviour
She has acquired a good knowledge of English.
He has acquired a reputation for dishonesty.

data.chText: 我最近开始喜欢吃橄榄了。
data.enText: I have recently acquired a taste for olives.
to obtain sth by buying or being given it
The company has just acquired new premises.

data.chText: 我突然有了一个继兄弟。

data.enText: a thing that you do not like much at first but gradually learn to like

data.chText: 要慢慢培养才会欣赏抽象艺术。
data.enText: Abstract art is an acquired taste.

simple_means.memory_skill: ac 加强 + quir 寻求；获得 + e → 获取

means: (通过努力、能力、行为表现)获得

ex.chText: 她获得了“国际女高音”的美名。
ex.enText: She gained a reputation as an international soprano.

ex.chText: 他最终获得了上校军衔。
ex.enText: He finally gained the rank of colonel.

synonyms.bx: 指通过后天努力或有目的的行动逐渐获得某种想要或需要的东西，如成就、利益等。

ex.chText: 这位百万富翁的财富是怎样得来的？
ex.enText: How did the millionaire acquire his wealth?

ex.chText: 他逐步获得了工作经验。
ex.enText: Step by step he acquired job experience.

synonyms.bx: 指通过自身持续不断的努力而获得某物，也指日积月累地获得知识、技能等。

ex.chText: 他终于当上了福特汽车公司的总裁。
ex.enText: He attained the position of President of Ford Motors.

ex.chText: 他为获得飞行员执照所下的苦功是值得赞扬的。
ex.enText: His painstaking efforts to attain his pilot's licence is praiseworthy.

synonyms.bx: 指通过长时间的艰苦努力而得到所需或盼望已久的东西，如成就、重要职位等。

ex.chText: 他们需要立即得到帮助。
ex.enText: They need to get help immediately.

ex.chText: 她获得朗诵比赛第一名。
ex.enText: She got first prize in the recitation contest.

ex.chText: 她的努力不但徒劳无功，反而惹来一身麻烦。
ex.enText: She got nothing but trouble for her efforts.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，可指以任何方式得到某物，并非一定要经过努力。

data.enText: a thing that you do not like much at first but gradually learn to like

data.chText: 要慢慢培养才会欣赏抽象艺术。
data.enText: Abstract art is an acquired taste.

tr: come to have or undergo a change of (physical features and attributes)
example: He grew a beard
The patient developed abdominal pains
I got funny spots all over my body
Well-developed breasts

tr: take on a certain form, attribute, or aspect
example: His voice took on a sad tone
The story took a new turn
he adopted an air of superiority
She assumed strange manners
The gods assume human or animal form in these fables
I acquired a strong aversion to television
Children must develop a sense of right and wrong
Dave developed leadership qualities in his new position
develop a passion for painting
She learned dancing from her sister
I learned Sanskrit
Children acquire language at an amazing rate

tr: come into the possession of something concrete or abstract
example: She got a lot of paintings from her uncle
They acquired a new pet
Get your results the next day
Get permission to take a few days off from work
I acquired a passing knowledge of Chinese
Gain an understanding of international finance

tr: locate (a moving entity) by means of a tracking system such as radar

value.def: If you acquire something, you buy or obtain it for yourself, or someone gives it to you.

example.ex: General Motors acquired a 50% stake in Saab for about $400m...
example.tran: 通用汽车公司以大约4亿美元的价格购得了萨博汽车公司50%的股份。

example.ex: I recently acquired some wood from a holly tree...
example.tran: 最近我从一棵冬青树上弄了些木料。

example.ex: She was sitting in her newly-acquired wheelchair.
example.tran: 她正坐在新买的轮椅上。

value.def: If you acquire something such as a skill or a habit, you learn it, or develop it through your daily life or experience.

example.ex: I've never acquired a taste for wine...
Having read the book, she will be able to pass on the acquired knowledge to trainee teachers.
example.tran: 读完此书，她便能将从书中所得传授给实习教师。

value.def: If someone or something acquires a certain reputation, they start to have that reputation.

example.ex: He has acquired a reputation as this country's premier solo violinist.
example.tran: 他已经赢得了该国首席小提琴独奏家的名誉。

value.def: If you describe something as an acquired taste, you mean that a lot of people do not like it when they first experience it, but often start to like it more when they get to know it better.

example.ex: Broad beans are very much an acquired taste...
example.tran: 要慢慢适应才能吃得惯蚕豆。

example.ex: Living alone is an acquired taste.
example.tran: 独处是一种修得的境界。

value.tran: 后天养成的爱好;培养出来的兴趣

trans: 争取顾客；争取客户；争取经销商
数据采集；资料取得；采集数据

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to seek, to obtain 寻求；获得
rootsaffixes.title: quest, quir, quis, quer

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + quir 寻求；获得 + e → 获取
acquir〔e〕获得；学识 + ed 表形容词 → 后天习得的
acquire 获取 + ment 表名词 → 获得；学识
ac 加强 + quis 寻求；获得 + itive …的 → 不断寻求 → 贪得的
con 加强 + quer 寻求；获得 → 获得 → 征服
con 共同 + quest 寻求；获得 → 获得 → 征服
dis 分散 + quis 寻求；获得 + ition 行为，状态，结果，由行为产生的事物 → 分开寻问 → 到处问 → 探究
in 加以… + quest 寻求；获得 → 加以询问 → 审问
in 加以… + quir 寻求；获得 + e → 加以询问 → 询问
in 加以… + quis 寻求；获得 + ition，inquire 的名词 → 调查，审问
pre 预先 + requisite 要素，要件 → 先决条件
quer 寻求；获得 + y 表行为 → 寻求答案 → 疑问
quest 寻求；获得 + ion 表名词 → 问题，疑问
re 一再 + quest 寻求；获得 → 因需求而一再要求 → 要求；恳请
re 一再 + quir 寻求；获得 + e → 一再要获得 → 要求 → 强制要求 → 命令
re 一再 + quis 寻求；获得 + ite 表物 → 一再需求的物品 → 必需品 →〔必需品是〕必要的
